1.List the Empno, Ename, Sal and 3 digit rounded Daily sal of all emps in the asc order of Annsal

ANS:- SELECT EMPNO, ENAME, round (SAL/30,3)"DAILY SAL" FROM EMP ORDER BY SAL 
  
  COLUMENAME should not be given  in the cotesan 

2.List the Empno, Ename, Sal of all emps working for Mgr 7369 

ANS:- SELECT EMPNO, ENAME, SAL FROM EMP WHERE MGR=7369

3.Display all the details of the emps whose Comm. Is more than their Sal 

ANS:- SELECT*FROM EMP WHERE SAL<COMM 

4.List the emps who does not belong to Deptno 20 

ANS:- SELECT*FROM EMP WHERE DEPTNO<>20

5.List the empno,ename,sal,deptno of the dept 10 emps in the ascending order of salary.

ANS:- SELECT EMPNO,ENAME,DEPTNO,SAL FROM EMP WHERE DEPTNO=10 ORDER BY SAL ASC

6.List the emps whose annual sal ranging from 23000 to 40000

ANS:- SELECT*FROM EMP WHERE SAL*12   BETWEEN 23000 AND 40000; 

7.List the emps working under the mgrs 7369,7890,7654,7900

ANS:- SELECT*FROM EMP WHERE MGR IN(7369,7890,7654,7900)

8.List the emps who are either ‘CLERK’ or ‘ANALYST’ in the Desc order of their salary.

ANS:- SELECT*FROM EMP WHERE (JOB='CLERK'OR JOB='ANALYST') ORDER BY SAL DESC
  
9.Find the analysts and managers (empno,ename,job,deptno) who’s salary is between 2000to 4000.

ANS:- SELECT EMPNO,ENAME,JOB,DEPTNO,SAL FROM EMP WHERE JOB IN('MANAGER','ANALYST') AND SAL between 2000 and 4000

10.Find the employees (empno,ename,hiredate,sal) who joned after 1982 and whose salary is greater than 1700 order by hiredate

ANS:- SELECT EMPNO,ENAME,HIREDATE,SAL FROM EMP WHERE HIREDATE>'31-DEC-82' AND SAL>1700 ORDER BY HIREDATE 

11.	Find out the all salesman and analyst who belong from deptno 10 or 20 and whose salary
is between 1500 to 2800.

ANS:- SELECT*FROM EMP WHERE JOB IN('SALESMAN','ANALYST')  AND (DEPTNO=10 OR DEPTNO=20)AND SAL BETWEEN 1500 and 2800


